title: Driver cut from car after crash and rushed to hospital
text:
Driver cut from car after crash in Netley Abbey Driver cut from car after crash and rushed to hospital 0 comments 
A MAN was cut from his car and taken to hospital after a crash in Hampshire. 
Firefighters from Hightown and Eastleigh stations were called to the scene of the crash on Wykenham Road, Netley Abbey, shortly before 7pm last night. Share article 
They helped release a male casualty from his car before he was transported to hospital by South Central Ambulance Service and the scene was cleared within an hour. 
Anyone with information on the incident is asked to contact Hampshire Constabulary on 101. Promoted Stories Driver cut from car after crash in Netley Abbey   Keep in touch with local news
